12 May 1997<br>
Good morning from a Sioux Vietnam Veteran, United States Marine Corps, 1st Battalion, 5th Marines, 1st Marine Division north of Chu Lai, 1966. Was just wondering how many of you that visit this site are American Indian. Most every book you read has some reference to knowing &quot;chief,&quot; or some such monicker. Guess there were quite a few of us over there.<br>
 Would welcome any comments regarding this interest. It would be quite an awesome gathering if we would invite all brothers, sisters who served or lived there to gather in the Black Hills of South Dakota to have a &quot;Wiping of the Tears&quot; ceremony, give thanks for still living, prayers for those who've passed on, and pray for peace in our time.<br>
 I remain with respect, in comradeship, Mitakuye Oyasin--All My Relatives, Tahunska Tanka--Big Leggins, aka Leonard Bruguier
